	   <tr><td colspan=2>If a bard goes toe to toe with any melee classes they are playing their character wrong (IMHO).&nbsp;&nbsp;I've had several friends who played bards and know several more who play on Rallos Zek as I used to play on there.  A bard can take on a melee.. or used to be able to but the trick is not to get into melee with them and wear them down to the point that you can take them.  Now, if the melee has good archery skills/equipment and a good bow it makes that a lot harder.  In the end it all depends on your experience and ability to play the particular class in question.  An inexperienced player with a necromancer may have incredibly powerful abilities but if they don't use them right or at all they're screwed.<br>&nbsp;<br>"Understanding is a three-edged sword: your side, their side .. and the truth."</td></tr>
